WEBVTT

00:22.800 --> 00:26.320
I now hasten to the more moving part of my story.

00:26.320 --> 00:33.140
I shall relate events that impressed me with feelings which, from what I had been, had made

00:33.140 --> 00:40.020
me what I am. Spring advanced rapidly and the weather became fine and the skies cloudless.

00:40.820 --> 00:44.600
It surprised me that what before was desert and gloomy should now bloom

00:44.600 --> 00:51.940
with the most beautiful flowers and verdure. My senses were gratified and refreshed by a thousand

00:51.940 --> 00:57.900
scents of delight and a thousand sights of beauty. It was on one of these days when my

00:57.900 --> 01:03.800
cottagers periodically rested from labor, the old man played on his guitar and the children listened

01:03.800 --> 01:09.760
to him, that I observed the countenance of Felix was melancholy beyond expression. He sighed

01:09.760 --> 01:16.680
frequently and once his father paused in his music and I conjectured by his manner that he

01:16.680 --> 01:24.040
the cause of the son's sorrow. Felix replied in a cheerful accent and the old man was recommencing

01:24.040 --> 01:30.320
his music when someone tapped at the door. It was a lady on horseback accompanied by a countryman

01:30.320 --> 01:36.680
as a guide. The lady was dressed in a dark suit and covered with a thick black veil. Agatha asked

01:36.680 --> 01:42.560
a question to which the stranger only replied by pronouncing in a sweet accent the name of Felix.

01:43.200 --> 01:46.640
Her voice was musical but unlike that of either of my friends.

01:47.480 --> 01:54.960
On hearing this word Felix came up hastily to the lady who when she saw him threw up her veil

01:54.960 --> 02:02.140
and I beheld a countenance of angelic beauty and expression. Her hair of shining raven black and

02:02.140 --> 02:08.680
curiously braided. Her eyes were dark but gentle though animated. Her features of a regular

02:08.680 --> 02:14.480
proportion and her complexion wondrously fair each cheek tingled with a lovely pink.

02:15.620 --> 02:21.240
Felix sometimes ravaged with delight when he saw her. Every trait of sorrow vanished from his face

02:21.240 --> 02:27.520
and it instantly expressed a degree of ecstatic joy of which I could hardly have believed capable.

02:28.140 --> 02:32.920
His eyes sparkled as his cheeks flushed with pleasure and at that moment I thought of him

02:32.920 --> 02:38.600
as beautiful as the stranger. She appeared affected by different feelings wiping a few

02:38.600 --> 02:43.740
tears from her lovely eyes. She held her hand out to Felix who kissed it rapturously

02:43.740 --> 02:50.500
and called her as well as I could distinguish his sweet Abraham. She did not appear to understand

02:50.500 --> 02:56.580
him but smiled. He assisted her to dismount and dismissing her guide conducted her into the

02:56.580 --> 03:02.140
cottage. Some conversation took place between him and his father and the young stranger now

03:02.140 --> 03:07.680
at the old man's feet and would have kissed his hand but he raised her and embraced her affectionately.

03:09.720 --> 03:14.940
I soon perceived that although the stranger uttered the articulate sounds and soon appeared

03:14.940 --> 03:21.080
to have a language of her own she was neither understood by nor herself understood the cottagers.

03:22.180 --> 03:27.620
They made many signs which I did not comprehend and I saw that her presence diffused gladness

03:27.620 --> 03:33.520
through the cottage dispelling their sorrow as the sun dissipates the morning mist. Felix

03:33.520 --> 03:39.940
seemed particularly happy and with smiles of delight welcomed his Abraham. Agatha the ever

03:39.940 --> 03:45.720
gentle Agatha kissed the hands of the lovely stranger and pointing to her brother made signs

03:45.720 --> 03:51.540
which appeared to me to mean that he had been sorrowful until she came. Some hours passed thus

03:51.540 --> 03:56.580
while they by their countenances expressed joy the cause of which I did not comprehend.

03:57.660 --> 04:03.060
Presently I found by the frequent recurrence of some sound which the stranger repeated after them

04:03.060 --> 04:08.520
that she was endeavoring to learn their language and the idea instantly occurred to me that I

04:08.520 --> 04:14.020
should make use of the same instructions to the same end. The stranger learned about 20 words at

04:14.020 --> 04:20.320
the first lesson most of them indeed were those which I had before understood but I profited by

04:20.320 --> 04:27.680
others. As night came on Agatha and the and the Arabian retired early when they separated Felix

04:27.680 --> 04:34.080
kissed the hand of the stranger and said good night sweet Safi. He sat up much longer conversing with

04:34.080 --> 04:40.020
his father and by the frequent repetition of her name I conjectured that their lovely guest was the

04:40.020 --> 04:46.520
subject of their conversation. I ardently desired to understand them and bent every faculty towards

04:46.520 --> 04:54.080
that purpose but found it utterly impossible. The next morning Felix went out to his work

04:54.080 --> 04:59.360
and after the usual occupations of Agatha were finished the Arabian sat at the feet of the old

04:59.360 --> 05:05.540
man and taking his guitar played some airs so entrancingly beautiful that they at once

05:05.540 --> 05:11.100
drew tears of sorrow and delight from my eyes. She sang and her voice flowed with a rich cadence

05:11.100 --> 05:17.160
swelling or dying like a night night like a nightingale of the woods. When she had finished

05:17.160 --> 05:22.560
she gave the guitar to Agatha who at first declined it. She played a simple air and her

05:22.560 --> 05:27.340
voice accompanied it in sweet accents but unlike the wondrous strain of the stranger

05:28.060 --> 05:33.860
the old man appeared enraptured and said some words with Agatha endeavored to explain to Safi

05:33.860 --> 05:38.980
and by which he appeared to wish to express that she bestowed on him the greatest delight by her

05:38.980 --> 05:46.000
music. The days now passed as peacefully as before with the sole alteration that joy had

05:46.000 --> 05:51.920
taken place of sadness and accountances of my friends. Safi was always gay and happy.

05:52.420 --> 05:57.720
She and I improved rapidly in the knowledge of language so that in two months I began to

05:57.720 --> 06:03.480
comprehend most of the words uttered by my protectors. In the meanwhile also the black

06:03.480 --> 06:08.360
ground was covered with herbage and the green banks interspersed with innumerable flowers

06:08.360 --> 06:14.860
sweet to the scent and the eyes stars of pale radiance among the moonlit woods. The sun became

06:14.860 --> 06:21.780
warmer the nights clear and balmy and my nocturnal ramblers rambles were an extreme pleasure to me

06:21.780 --> 06:26.200
although they were considerably shortened by the late setting and early rising of the sun

06:26.200 --> 06:31.220
for I never ventured abroad during daylight fearful of meeting with the same treatment

06:31.220 --> 06:34.200
I had formerly endured at the first village which I entered.

06:36.280 --> 06:41.700
My days were spent in close attention that I might more speedily master the language

06:41.700 --> 06:46.960
and that I may boast and I may boast that I improved more rapidly than the Arabian

06:46.960 --> 06:52.660
who understood very little and conversed in broken accents whilst I comprehended and can

06:52.660 --> 06:59.200
imitate almost every word that was spoken. While I improved in speech I also learned the science of

06:59.200 --> 07:04.180
letters as it was taught to the stranger and this opened before me a wide range of words

07:04.180 --> 07:10.920
a wide field for wonder and delight. The book from which Felix instructed Safi was Volney's

07:10.920 --> 07:17.360
Ruins of Empires. I should not have understood the purport of this book had not Felix in reading it

07:17.360 --> 07:22.660
gave very minute explanations. He had chosen this work he said because the

07:22.660 --> 07:29.020
the clamatory style was framed in imitation of the eastern authors though this work I obtained

07:29.020 --> 07:35.240
through this work I obtained a curious knowledge of history and a view of the several empires at

07:35.240 --> 07:40.580
present existing in the world. It gave me an insight into the manners governments and religions

07:40.580 --> 07:46.780
of the different nations of the earth. I heard of the slothful Asiatics of the

07:46.780 --> 07:59.000
stupendous genius and mental activity of the Grecians of the war and wondrous virtue of the

07:59.000 --> 08:04.280
chivalry Christianity and kings. I heard of the discovery of the American hemisphere

08:04.280 --> 08:09.840
and wept with Safi over the hapless fate of its of its original inhabitants.

08:11.520 --> 08:17.940
These wonderful narrations inspired me with strange feelings was man indeed at once so powerful so

08:17.940 --> 08:24.660
virtuous and magnificent yet so vicious and base. He appeared at one time the mere scion of evil

08:24.660 --> 08:30.440
of the evil principle and at another as all that can be conceived of noble and godlike.

08:31.120 --> 08:35.760
To be a great and virtuous man appeared the highest honor that can befall a sensitive being.

08:36.480 --> 08:43.400
To be based and vicious as many on record have been appeared the lowest

08:44.580 --> 08:50.420
degration a condition more object that than that of the blind mole or harmless worm.

08:51.180 --> 08:55.840
For a long time I could not conceive how one man could go forth to murder his fellow

08:55.840 --> 09:01.760
or even why there were laws and governments but when I heard details of the vice and bloodshed

09:01.760 --> 09:08.400
my wonder ceased and I turned away with disgust and loathing. Every conversation of the cottagers

09:08.400 --> 09:15.280
now opened new wonders to me. While I listened to the instructors instructions with Felix bestowed

09:15.280 --> 09:22.180
upon the Arabian the strange system of human society was explained to me. I heard of the division

09:22.180 --> 09:28.400
of property of immense wealth and squalid poverty of rank descent and noble blood.

09:29.080 --> 09:34.980
The words introduced me to turn towards myself. I learned that the possessions most esteemed by

09:34.980 --> 09:42.280
your fellow creatures were high and unsullied descent united with riches. A man might be

09:42.280 --> 09:47.760
respected with only one of these advantages but without either he was considered except in very

09:47.760 --> 09:54.040
rare instances as a vagabond and a slave doomed to waste his powers for the profits of the chosen

09:54.040 --> 10:01.540
few. And what was I of my creation and creator I was absolutely ignorant but I knew that I possess

10:01.540 --> 10:09.260
no money no friends no kind of property. I was beside endured with a hideously figured a figure

10:09.260 --> 10:16.660
hideously deformed and lonesome. I was not even the same nature as man. I was more agile than they

10:16.660 --> 10:22.480
and could subsist on upon a coarser diet. I bore the extremities of heat and coal with less injury

10:22.480 --> 10:29.780
to my frame and my stature far exceeded theirs. When I looked around I saw and heard of none like

10:29.780 --> 10:37.300
me. Was I then a monster a blot upon the earth from which all men fled and whom all men disowned?

10:38.060 --> 10:42.580
I cannot describe to you the agony that these reflections inflicted upon me.

10:42.960 --> 10:49.300
I tried to dispel them but sorrow only increased with knowledge. Oh that I had forever remained

10:49.300 --> 10:56.120
in my native wood nor known nor felt beyond the sensations of hunger thirst and heat.

10:57.260 --> 11:02.540
Of what a strange nature is knowledge it clings to the mind when it is once seized on it like a light

11:02.540 --> 11:08.860
on a rock. I had sometimes wished to shake off all thought and feeling but I learned that it

11:08.860 --> 11:14.780
was only one means to overcome the sensation of pain and that was death a state of which I feared

11:14.780 --> 11:21.580
yet did not understand. I admired virtue and good feelings and loved the gentle manners and admirable

11:21.580 --> 11:27.260
qualities of my cottagers but I was shut off from the intercourse with them except through means

11:27.260 --> 11:33.600
which I obtained by stealth when I was unseen and unknown which rather increased than satisfied

11:33.600 --> 11:41.480
the desire I had of becoming one of my fellows. The gentle words of Agatha and the animated smiles

11:41.480 --> 11:47.680
of the charming Arabian were not for me. The mild exhortations of the old man and the lively

11:47.680 --> 11:53.400
conversation of the loved Felix were not for me. Miserable unhappy wrench.

11:55.640 --> 12:01.600
Other lessons were impressed upon me even more deeply. I heard of the differences between the

12:01.600 --> 12:06.680
sexes and the birth and growth of children. How the father doted on the smiles of the infant

12:06.680 --> 12:13.300
and the lively sallies of the older child. How all life and cares of the mother were wrapped up in

12:13.300 --> 12:19.600
precious charge. How the mind of youth expanded and gained knowledge of brother sister and all

12:19.600 --> 12:26.000
various relationships which bind one human being to another in mutual bonds. But where were my

12:26.000 --> 12:31.780
friends in relations? No father had watched my infant days. No mother had blessed me with smiles

12:31.780 --> 12:39.000
or caresses. Nor if they had all my past life was now a blot a blind vacancy in which I distinguished

12:39.000 --> 12:47.160
nothing. From my earliest remembrance I had been as I then was in height and proportion.

12:47.700 --> 12:54.600
I had never yet seen a being resembling me or who claimed any intercourse with me. What was I?

12:54.920 --> 13:01.300
The question returned only to be answered with groans. I will soon explain to what those feelings

13:01.300 --> 13:07.420
tended but allow me to return to the cottagers whose story excited me in such various feeling

13:07.420 --> 13:13.400
of indignation delight and wonder but which all terminated in innocent love and reverence for my

13:13.400 --> 13:22.000
protectors. For so I loved in an innocent half painful self-deceit to call them. End of chapter 13.

